name: TCGA GBM Classifiers
desc: Gene expression-based molecular classification of GBM subtypes (Proneural, Neural, Classical, Mesenchymal)

name: Glioma Markers
desc: Genes recurrently impacted in TCGA gliomas

name: TCGA Pancan Mutated
desc: Significantly mutated genes according to the TCGA PANCAN working group (syn1750331) identified by both MuSiC and MutSig

name: Oncoplex Vogelstein
desc: Combined set from the Oncoplex gene panel and driver genes described in Vogelstein, Science 2013.

name: Oncoplex
desc: A sequencing panel that detects mutations in genes related to cancer treatment, prognosis, and diagnosis.

name: OSCC Expression Markers
desc: Differentially expressed probe set comparing normal oral tissue to oral squamous cell carcinoma

name: Breast PAM50
desc: Gene expression based subtype predictor for subtypes luminal A, luminal B, HER2-enriched, and basal-like

name: Breast Tumor Intrinsic Classifier
desc: Meta analysis of available breast cancer gene expression datasets grouping LumA, LumB, Basal-like, HER2+/ER-, and Normal Breast-like tumor subtypes

name: FoundationOne Heme
desc: FoundationOne® Heme is designed to analyze and interpret sequence information for somatically altered genes in human hematologic malignancies (leukemias, lymphomas, and myelomas), and sarcomas. Genes included in this assay encode known or likely targets of therapies, either approved or in clinical trials, or otherwise known drivers of oncogenesis.

name: TCGA Sarcoma alterations
desc: Frequently mutated genes in soft-tissue sarcoma subtypes

name: Sarcoma markers
desc: Compiled from multiple publications on different sarcoma subtypes

name: Sarcoma CINSARC
desc: Performed genomic and expression profiling in a training set of 183 sarcomas and established a prognostic gene expression signature, complexity index in sarcomas (CINSARC), composed of 67 genes related to mitosis and chromosome management
